<h2 class="nounderline"><a name="maincontent">Employment</a></h2>

<h3>Employment of Handicapped</h3>
<p>
<a class="resource" href="http://www.disabilityindia.org/selfEmployment.cfm">http://www.disabilityindia.org/selfEmployment.cfm</a><br />
Assistance to disabled persons in finding gainful employment either through Special Cells in normal Employment Exchanges or through Special Employment Exchanges for physically handicapped persons
<a href="http://socialjustice.nic.in/disabled/welcome.htm">http://socialjustice.nic.in/disabled/welcome.htm
</a>
</p>

<h3>Help Handicap</h3>
<p>
<a href="http://www.helphandicap.org">http://www.helphandicap.org</a>
</p>

<h3>National Awards for People with Disabilities</h3>
<p>
<a class="resource" href="http://socialjustice.nic.in/disabled/welcome.htm">http://socialjustice.nic.in/disabled/welcome.htm</a><br />
The Ministry of Social Justice &amp; Empowerment has been giving National Awards 
since 1969 on International Day of Disabled Persons. December 3, the Awards are given in different categories,   namely best employer of disabled, outstanding employee, placement officer, best individual, institution, barrier-free environment, creative disabled person and National Technology Awards involved in the rehabilitation and welfare of persons with disabilities.
</p>

<h3>Scheme of National Awards for Welfare of Persons with Disability</h3>
<p>
<a class="resource" href="http://socialjustice.nic.in/disabled/welcome.htm">http://socialjustice.nic.in/disabled/welcome.htm</a><br />
In 1969, the Government of India approved a Scheme for giving National Awards to the outstanding employers of persons with disabilities as well as the most outstanding employees. The scheme has been subsequently amended to include awards to placement officers, eminent individuals, outstanding institutions, and for outstanding inventions by technologists.
</p>

<h3>Schools for the Blind and Vocational Training Centers</h3>
<p>
<a class="resource" href="http://webelmediatronics.in/brlads/govt_maharashtra.htm">http://webelmediatronics.in/brlads/govt_maharashtra.htm</a><br />
</p>

<h3>National Society for Equal Opportunities for the Handicapped (NASEOH)</h3>
<p>
<a class="resource" href="http://www.ashanet.org/projects/project-view.php?p=248">http://www.ashanet.org/projects/project-view.php?p=248</a><br />
NASEOH, India was founded in 1968 and works towards the betterment of all categories of disabled people. 
It provides equal opportunities for education, vocational training, work and recreation.
</p>


<h3>National Handicapped Finance and Development Corporation (NHFDC)</h3>
<p>
<a class="resource" href="http://socialjustice.nic.in/disabled/welcome.htm ">http://socialjustice.nic.in/disabled/welcome.htm </a><br />
The objectives of NHFDC include providing concessional finance for a wide range of activities including self-employment ventures, upgrading of skills, assistance for infra-structural activities which support economic pursuits, loans for education etc. Assistance is given to disabled persons who are below double the poverty line.
</p>

<h3>Grant-in-Aid Schemes of the Ministry of Social Justice &amp; Empowerment</h3>
<p>
<a class="resource" href="http://www.disabilityindia.org/aidscheme.cfm">http://www.disabilityindia.org/aidscheme.cfm</a><br />
The different Grant-in-Aid schemes offered.
</p>

<h3>Provisions in Schemes Offered by the Ministry of Rural Areas &amp; Employment</h3>
<p>
Indira Awas Yojana <a href="http://www.disabilityindia.org/IAY.cfm">http://www.disabilityindia.org/IAY.cfm</a><br />
Jawahar Rojgar Yojna <a href="http://www.disabilityindia.org/JRY.cfm">http://www.disabilityindia.org/JRY.cfm</a><br />
Sanghas in Rural Areas <a href="http://www.disabilityindia.org/sanghas.cfm">http://www.disabilityindia.org/sanghas.cfm</a><br />
Poverty Alleviation Programs <a href="http://www.disabilityindia.org/povertyalleviation.cfm">http://www.disabilityindia.org/povertyalleviation.cfm</a>
</p>

<h3>Compensations and Retirement Benefits</h3>
<p>
Disability Due to Accident 
<a href="http://www.disabilityindia.org/accidents.cfm">http://www.disabilityindia.org/accidents.cfm</a><br />
Disability Pensions 
<a href="http://www.disabilityindia.org/disabilitypension.cfm">http://www.disabilityindia.org/disabilitypension.cfm</a>
</p>

<h3>Ali Yavar Jung National Institute for the Hearing Handicapped Jobs for the 
Deaf</h3>
<p>
<a class="resource" href="http://www.jobsfordeaf.nic.in/">http://www.jobsfordeaf.nic.in/</a><br />
This site is dedicated to helping the hearing impaired/handicapped in their search for gainful employment. The goal is to make access to jobs for deaf people easier throughout India. There is no charge for the job applicants or 
employers.</p>

